  <div class="col-md-7">
    <p> Now that we were all out of the water again, the technology was broken down into its individual parts and I had dropped out of the neoprene skin. I have never been to the outdoor pool after a day like today. I only tortured myself back to my car and watched a film. </p>
    <p> Yesterday we went to the first two dives in the open sea. After we quickly collected our equipment in the morning, we only drove a few minutes to the nearest diving spot Gordon's Bay. There we tortured ourselves in our equipment when it rains and started. After about 200 meters we finally arrived at the water. I can tell you 200 meters in full diving equipment are not a walk. What I didn't know that later would wait for me even tougher paths into the water. </p>
    <p> Once at the water, it turned out that the path into the 22 degree warm water was not easy because there were a few waves. Since the water was warmer than the air, I was happy to finally get into the water. After we all helped each other in deeper water, the training continued. Only this time it was much nicer because we were surrounded by many beautiful and colorful fish during the exercises on the surface. </p>
    <p> A young Asian in my group could be seen that she was not comfortable. Do only a few minutes in the water and before we dived, she decided to cancel the dive and return to the base alone. </p>
  </div>
