  <div class="col-md-7">
    <p> We waited until she was out of the water before we finally dived into the beautiful underwater world. With a pleasant 5 meters of view, we went to the exercises that we had discussed before the dive. After we got through it, we remained a little air to enjoy the wildlife down there. Even a very large blue grouper showed up. Blue Grouper have a great similarity to carp only that they are blue like gemstones. As I should learn in the meeting after the dive, this special fish even has a name. His name is Elvis. Elvis because he supposedly caught and declared to death but kept appearing. </p>
    <p> At the second dive of the day, we spent even more time under the water surface. Overall, I came up with my equipment for 38 minutes according to the computer. The exercises were not the most difficult again. This time it was about situations when you get out of the air. The trainer turned the air under water to a participant and then checked the correct behavior of the diver and its buddy up to the water surface. </p>
    <p> Now that we were through the second dive, we went into the water again without a bottle but with a vest to do a few exercises with the snorkel. Then we went back to the diving school to clean our equipment and plan the next day. In the evening I wasn't in the bucket like the day before. I didn't do much again, since there was still a diving day ahead of me. </p>
  </div>
</div><div class="row margin-bottom-10">
  <div class="col-md-12">
    <p> This morning there was briefing what will happen today and then it started again to two more dives in a different place than yesterday. Today we went to the La Perouse district. From there we wanted to make two dives around the island of Bare Island. The island and the diving spot are known for two things. First, every mission Impossible 2 fan knows the island because a large part of the film was shot on the island. Second, you should be able to meet seahorses and harmless Port Jackson Haie around the island. </p>
  </div>
